          • Title: VP of Finance & Accounting
          • Salary: $180K - $200K + Equity + Bonus
          • Requirements: 7+ years exp in finance and accounting
          • Location: San Fransisco, CA (Hybrid)


          Our client, a passionate in-game ad-tech startup, is seeking a VP of Finance & Accounting to oversee their financial planning and accounting operations. The individual in this role should be proactive with company finances, be commercially aware, and be prepared to provide in-depth guidance on the best path of growth for their business.


          Responsibilities


          • Provide strategic financial leadership by collaborating with executive team to set financial objectives, strategies, and plans aligned with company goals
          • Oversee financial planning/analysis process, including budgeting, forecasting, and long-term financial modeling
          • Establish internal KPIs (Key Performance Indicators) to measure financial performance and operational efficiency - providing insights for decision-making and growth tracking
          • Lead establishment of a robust reporting/analytics function, generating actionable insights from financial/operational data to support business decisions
          • Prepare comprehensive board packages, financial presentations, and other materials for executive-level meetings/investor updates
          • Serve as a liaison with investors - managing relationships and communication to ensure alignment on financial performance, fundraising, and strategic initiatives
          • Manage all accounting functions - including accounts payable, accounts receivable, general ledger, and financial statement preparation
          • Develop/implement policies and procedures to safeguard company assets and ensure efficient financial operations
          • Evaluate/optimize capital allocation strategies to support growth and maximize returns for investors


          Requirements


          • 7+ years of experience in finance and accounting roles - with at least 2 years in a leadership capacity
          • Bachelor's degree in Accounting/Finance - CPA preferred
          • Experience working within high-growth, VC-backed companies is highly preferred
          • Proven track record in financial planning and analysis, budgeting, and strategic financial management
          • Strong knowledge of GAAP/ financial reporting requirements and hands-on experience overseeing day-to-day accounting operations
          • Excellent relational/communication skills with high emotional intelligence and a passion for people development
          • Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to communicate complex financial information in a clear and concise manner


          Benefits


          • Salary of $180K - $200K + Equity + Bonus
          • Health/Dental/Vision Insurance
          • Unlimited PTO
          • 401k Matching
          • Join a progressive, open-minded company - and play video games!
